                                                                    <h3>124. Al-Multazam and Prayers Near This Place</h3>
                                    <a href="../../../../external.html?link=https://thaqalayn.net/book/4" class="btn btn-primary"><span data-feather="arrow-left-circle"></span> Back to book</a>
                                                                <hr>
                                                            <p class="libAr" dir="rtl">1ـ عِدَّةٌ مِنْ أَصْحَابِنَا عَنْ سَهْلِ بْنِ زِيَادٍ عَنْ أَحْمَدَ بْنِ مُحَمَّدِ بْنِ أَبِي نَصْرٍ عَنِ الْعَلاءِ بْنِ رَزِينٍ عَنْ مُحَمَّدِ بْنِ مُسْلِمٍ عَنْ أَبِي جَعْفَرٍ (عَلَيْهِ السَّلاَم) قَالَ قُلْتُ لَهُ مِنْ أَيْنَ أَسْتَلِمُ الْكَعْبَةَ إِذَا فَرَغْتُ مِنْ طَوَافِي قَالَ مِنْ دُبُرِهَا.</p>
                                <br>
                                
                                                            <p class="" dir="">1. A number of our people have narrated from Sahl ibn Ziyad from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn abu Nasr from al-‘Ala’ ibn Razin from Muhammad ibn Muslim who has said the following: “I asked abu Ja‘far, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, ‘What part of al-Ka‘bah should I touch after completing my Tawaf?’ He (the Imam) said, ‘You should touch its backside.”’ </p>
